docs.abstract: A new letter sent by independent designers to fashion executives demands reform, or at least a serious conversation about race.
docs.snippet: A new letter sent by independent designers to fashion executives demands reform, or at least a serious conversation about race.
docs.lead_paragraph: The designer Stella Jean wanted to make something clear about an impassioned letter she sent to Italian fashion’s governing body: “It’s not a protest,” she said. “I’m not protesting. It’s a proposal.”

headline.main: Italian Fashion Hasn’t Changed Enough, Black Designers Say

docs.abstract: The social network said it was designating the antigovernment movement as a dangerous organization.
docs.snippet: The social network said it was designating the antigovernment movement as a dangerous organization.
docs.lead_paragraph: Facebook said on Tuesday that it took down a network of accounts, groups and pages connected to an antigovernment movement in the United States that encourages violence.

docs.abstract: Talk about a Hollywood twist ending. “Moonlight” took best picture, but not until after it was mistakenly announced that “La La Land” had won.
docs.snippet: Talk about a Hollywood twist ending. “Moonlight” took best picture, but not until after it was mistakenly announced that “La La Land” had won.
docs.lead_paragraph: • “Moonlight” is best picture. In a bewildering end to the show, “La La Land” was first announced as the winner before its jubilant cast and crew were interrupted with a scarcely believable correction.

headline.main: ‘Moonlight,’ ‘La La Land’ and Everything Else That Happened at the Oscars
headline.print_headline: A Real Surprise Ending: ‘Moonlight’ Wins Best Picture

docs.abstract: His move to the University of Colorado is understandable in the college football world, but that doesn’t mean it can’t hurt given the pledges he had made to his historically Black institution.
docs.snippet: His move to the University of Colorado is understandable in the college football world, but that doesn’t mean it can’t hurt given the pledges he had made to his historically Black institution.
docs.lead_paragraph: Deion Sanders is doing what virtually every college football coach in America would do if given a chance: He is leaving success at a smaller school with limited options for the promised land of better facilities, better support, a deeper bench of more talented players and a chance to play on a bigger stage.

headline.main: Deion Sanders Leaving Jackson State Is No Surprise in the Coaching World
headline.print_headline: Easy to Be Disappointed in Sanders’s Move, but Hard to Be Surprised

docs.abstract: A Super Bowl ad by Ram had viewers openly wondering whether the company really used Dr. King’s words about the value of service to sell vehicles.

headline.main: Ram Trucks Commercial With Martin Luther King Jr. Sermon Is Criticized

docs.abstract: While mayors and police chiefs welcome federal oversight of the police, unions say it keeps officers from doing their jobs and makes the public less safe.
docs.snippet: While mayors and police chiefs welcome federal oversight of the police, unions say it keeps officers from doing their jobs and makes the public less safe.
docs.lead_paragraph: Black pedestrians in Baltimore stopped without reasonable suspicion. Black drivers in Ferguson, Mo., searched much more frequently than whites. Cleveland residents punched and kicked by officers and subjected to stun guns, without posing any threat.
